The paper discusses the limitations of algorithms that ensure post hoc generalization, which is a concept closely related to machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper presents lower bounds on the error of algorithms. The paper also discusses statistical queries, which falls under the sub-category of cs.ST (Statistics). Finally, the paper discusses the composition properties of post hoc generalization algorithms, which is a topic related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
